# Credentials written into the workspace by google-github-actions/auth.
# `cleanup_credentials` (default true) removes this in the job's post-step, but
# the file exists DURING the job, so any `git add -A` mid-job (e.g. an auto-fix
# or smoke step that commits) would otherwise capture it. Per the action's
# official guidance (google-github-actions/auth README, Issue #298), ignore it.
gha-creds-*.json
